        "section_value": "Chief Complaint\nFollow-up of chronic problems and to discuss medication effectiveness.\nHistory of Present Illness\nThe patient reports significant relief from reflux symptoms since starting protonix. He has made dietary modifications, including reducing caffeine and spicy foods. He reports improved mood and ability to perform his job effectively. He denies any chest pain, shortness of breath, or abdominal pain. He reports no symptoms at all.\nFindings\nVital signs are stable. Physical examination reveals 1+ pitting edema bilaterally in the lower extremities. A slight 2/6 systolic ejection murmur is auscultated, which is stable. No carotid bruits are present. Lung sounds are clear bilaterally. Endoscopy revealed mild gastritis.\nAssessment\nChronic reflux, managed with protonix. Mild lower extremity edema.\nPlan\nContinue protonix 40 mg daily. Advise continued dietary modifications. Schedule follow-up in four weeks to assess edema and medication effectiveness. The nurse will check vital signs and complete a focused physical exam.",
